President Muhammadu Buhari, on Saturday, returned to Abuja from his hometown in Daura, Katsina state. Buhari had travelled to Daura on July 8 for the Eid-el-Kabir celebration. Mohammed Bello, minister of the federal capital territory (FCT), was among persons who received Buhari at the Nnamdi Azikiwe international airport, Abuja. See pictures below. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-725180" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/FB_IMG_1657999266169.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="480" /> <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-725181" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/FB_IMG_1657999273425.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="511" /> <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-725182" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/FB_IMG_1657999409718.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="482" /> <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-725183" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/FB_IMG_1657999422666.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="480" /> 